keyValuePair.Value: You were completely in command. What set your team apart?
Two great wins against %1s and you were in complete control of both games. People were expecting a much closer-run thing. What did your team do to make it through to the next round in such style?
The team has great desire.

We work hard, of course. But there's also something special in this dressing room. Real desire. I think you saw that in both legs of this tie. And we want to improve. Our defending can be better. It'll need to be in the next round, for sure.
We're so confident on the ball.

The lads are playing very well at the moment. Individually and collectively. We look really confident on the ball. The man in possession always has plenty of options. That's what allowed us to dominate both legs of this tie so completely.

The lads are playing very well at the moment. Individually and collectively. We look really confident on the ball. The man in possession always has plenty of options. That's what allowed us to dominate both legs of this tie so completely.
I want us to get into the habit of winning.

There's a good spirit around the team at the moment. Winning games breeds confidence and I think we all saw that over the two legs of this tie. I want us to take that self-belief into our other games now before the next round.
Getting to the semi-final will surely lift the team's confidence?
You're through to the semis. You're probably as happy about the team's performances in both legs against %1s as you are about the results. Will these wins boost the boys' confidence even more?
These boys are driving each other on.

This is a highly-motivated group of players who really want to achieve something at this club. They're convinced they can win silverware this season. I want them to demand the best from each other in every game from now on.
The lads just want to play the next game!

When you're playing as well as we are at the moment, you just can't wait for the next game. The lads are happy to have reached the semi-final but they're already focused on our next fixture. That hunger can drive us on for the rest of the season, I hope.
We'll take some stopping!

I'm sure the lads will be looking forward to the semi-final. There's a great spirit in the dressing room. I think that's reflected in the way we approach games. We look dangerous going forward. Everybody wants to be involved. It'll take a good side to stop us now!
This great run goes on! Can you lift the trophy?
It's been a sensational run of form. Two more convincing wins in the semis and now you're through to the Final. Is there any stopping your boys at the moment?
We want to win trophies!

This is why we play football: to compete for the big trophies. We've given ourselves a real chance now. There's a real belief in the dressing room at the moment. We feel we can compete with anyone and the lads' knowing that drives us all on.
The Final can wait!

We're playing with so much confidence at the moment, we can't wait for the next game. It's great to be through to a cup final but, right now, all we're thinking about is how we can prepare ourselves for our next match in the league.
I hope our fans are enjoying the ride.

We played some great football and, definitely, we deserve to be in the Final. The supporters will enjoy the day, I'm sure. Credit to the senior players. They're the ones who've been inspiring us all with their commitment and determination. Real leaders.
How pleased are you with qualifying across these two games?
You've put in two very impressive performances and deserve to have qualified, without a doubt. Maybe the opposition weren't the highest standard, though. What do you expect from now on?
We know this journey's just beginning.

You can only beat what's in front of you so don't underestimate the boys' achievement in qualifying. But we know this is where the hard work starts. Don't worry. My players are well are aware that they'll be facing much stiffer tests from now on.
We knew we were good enough.

We were confident of going through and maybe we've silenced a few doubters now. But we want to impress in every competition we enter so, for now, all I'm thinking about is preparing for our next game as well as we can.
Great attacking display, wasn't it?

I hope our fans enjoyed that. We set this as an important target, qualifying over these two games. We've done that now, thanks to some excellent approach play and ruthless finishing. We want to win, of course, but we want entertain our supporters as well.

I hope our fans enjoyed that. We set this as an important target, qualifying over these two games. We've done that now, thanks to some excellent approach play and ruthless finishing. We want to win, of course, but we want entertain our supporters as well.
Are you happy enough with the draw today?
The hard work had already been done with that big win in the first leg. Are you happy enough to be through? Were you satisfied with the way the team finished off the job today?
We were intent on qualifying.

We were desperate to qualify. I saw good professionalism and good desire from my team today. The lads were great in the first leg. And this was just about finishing the job. We need to be playing in this competition every season, I believe.

We were desperate to qualify. I saw good professionalism and good desire from my team today. The lads were great in the first leg. And this was just about finishing the job. We need to be playing in this competition every season, I believe.
We're aware that this is only the start.

That was a very steady and disciplined performance. But we know we'll have to step up a level now. Every team we could meet in the competition from here on will have attacking players who can hurt us if we're not at our best.
We expect this of ourselves.
Well done to the boys on a professional job but, really, this is the minimum I expect from my team. We're just getting started in this competition. I want us to improve in every game from now on.
You're safely through. What can we expect from your boys now?

Today's draw completed the job after that big win in the first leg. Your lads have done well to go through and seem to be improving game by game. Can we expect them to push onto the next level in time for the next round?
I hope our fans are proud of the team.

We were definitely the better side over the two games. The boys looked to me to be in control for most of the tie and we made the most of our good possession. We're growing as a team and I hope our fans are enjoying watching us at the moment.

We were definitely the better side over the two games. The boys looked to me to be in control for most of the tie and we made the most of our good possession. We're growing as a team and I hope our fans are enjoying watching us at the moment.
We'll keep going and see what happens.
I'm pleased we're through. The tie was won with that great display in the first leg. Now, we'll just move on. The next game is always the most important one!
We'll dig in when we need to.

We're a team that's set up to play attacking football. But that doesn't work unless we're well-organised defensively, too. We have to be able to dig in and make ourselves difficult to play against. The boys know they'll be up against better players from now on in this competition.
Are you confident you can make the Final?
After that big win in the first leg, there was never much doubt about your boys claiming a place in the semis. Your playing well. Do you think this team can now make it through to the Final?
We're dangerous going forward.

Whoever we play in the semi-final, we know we'll be in for a tough game. The lads are looking like they can score against anybody at the moment. Great approach play, clever passing, getting men into the box. We're happy having the opposition worry about us.
We need to be consistent now.

We've got a good spirit and I think we've got a way of playing that suits the group. We're aggressive, positive with the ball and direct when we need to be. I want the lads to be on the front foot in every game now. We're all after the same thing, aren't we?
Let's see who we play.

I'm delighted we've made the semi-finals. That's a big step forward for these players. I'm confident they're a match for anybody. But let's see who we're drawn against before we start talking about reaching the Final!
You're into the Final. Can you go on and win the trophy now?

That was a very professional display today. After the big win in the first leg, your boys kept calm and played out the draw to book your place in the Final. How confident are you that you can go on and win the trophy?
We believe in ourselves, that's for sure.

The senior lads have been key to our success so far. They're strong mentally and they make sure every player knows his job. I'm confident going into every game at the moment. I hope we're ready to meet every challenge. I don't think this team will let the fans down.

The senior lads have been key to our success so far. They're strong mentally and they make sure every player knows his job. I'm confident going into every game at the moment. I hope we're ready to meet every challenge. I don't think this team will let the fans down.
We've got a winning mentality.
A team can get into the habit of winning games. I know we had to settle for a draw today but we'd already done the hard work in this tie. I like our attitude. Let's see how we do in the Final now.
It's about winning games.

I'm not really in the business of making predictions. The Final will be a one-off, a special occasion for everyone connected with the club. We're good enough to win, I'm sure. We'll just have to see if we can handle the pressure.
You've made it. Are you happy? Or relieved?
After your comfortable win in the first leg, everyone thought today's game would be a formality. But the opposition gave it a real go. Are you happy enough with how your boys handled the situation?
Getting through is all that matters.

We're a little disappointed with ourselves, in all honesty. Perhaps we should have been more positive in our attitude today. But I'm pleased with our hard work and our togetherness. Those are the qualities that have got us over the line. We're through. That's what counts.
We played like we thought the tie was over.

We got a great result in the first leg but we were disappointing today. We made a lot of poor decisions and gave the ball away too often in dangerous areas. Our attitude wasn't right. That won't be good enough if we want to go any further in the competition.
Let's move onto the next game.
I'm not too concerned with result today, even though it was disappointing for our fans. We did the hard work in the first leg. Now all I'm thinking about is preparing for our next game in the league.
Was that trickier than it should have been?
It looked as if you would coast into the semis after your first leg win. But today was a real struggle. Were you worried at any point that the tie might slip away from you?
We deserve our place in the semis.

We certainly weren't at our best. Was it fatigue? Was it thinking the job was already done? At least we dug inn when we had to and made sure we held onto our advantage. We're through now and reaching the semis is a real achievement for the team. We deserve it.
We have to be positive in our approach.

This is a team that's at its best when we're taking the game to the opposition. Yes, we had a comfortable lead, but we should have looked to build on that. Instead we got stuck in our own defensive third. We didn't get forward enough to create any chances. We've got to be positive every time we play.
Yes, it was a little nervy today!
We made life difficult for ourselves today but I was always confident we'd see it through. We're happy to have reached the semi-final. Now we have to turn all our attention to our next league game.
It was tense, but you must be happy to be in the Final?
In the end, you had to be grateful for the big win in the first leg. Today the boys looked short of confidence and ideas. Can you be sure which team will turn up in the Final now?
Well done to the boys on reaching the Final.

It's the quality of our attacking play that's got us into the Final. Today we felt the pressure a bit. We looked a little inhibited in our passing. But I'm sure we'll be more positive and play a bit freer on the big day. I want them to enjoy it. I believe these boys can win us the trophy.
Reaching the Final is a huge achievement.

We were on the brink of something special today and I think the occasion got to the players. We looked nervous. We weren't adventurous enough on the ball. I just hope we'll have got this poor display out of our system in time for the Final.
We can be proud of reaching the Final.

We would have wanted to put on a better display for our fans but the important thing is that we're through to the Final. Nobody, now, is going to remember how we got there. It'll be all about how we perform on the big day.
You're through but is there room for improvement?
You've gone through on aggregate after that great first leg win. But did you see worrying signs in today's performance? Are you confident your boys can handle the big occasions?
We can adapt to situations.

In both legs, I was pleased with how the players adapted to how the game was going. They dug in when they needed to but tried to be positive when we had the ball. They're intelligent lads and I trust them to find a way of winning. I'm pleased with their attitude.
We were hanging on at the end!

Look, we're through and that's great. But if we want to progress in this competition, we're going to have to be better-organised and much more resilient. We can't afford the kind of mistakes we made today which almost let the opposition back into the tie.
We can be better than this.

It wasn't pretty today, that's for sure! But the important thing is we're through. We have so many games to play we need to put this one behind us and turn all our attention to the next. We'll improve.
Is this one of your worst-ever defeats?
You thought you'd done the hard work in the first leg but today you had no answers once the opposition got back in the game. How can you explain what happened?
I'll take responsibility for it.
I'll take responsibility for it.

We played well in the first leg but I made the decision to go with a defensive shape today. That handed the initiative to the opposition, I guess. The momentum in the tie shifted and we just had no answers.

We played well in the first leg but I made the decision to go with a defensive shape today. That handed the initiative to the opposition, I guess. The momentum in the tie shifted and we just had no answers.
We've let ourselves down.

I was confident we'd be able to defend our lead from the first leg but, once they scored their first goal, we went to pieces. We were a mess. Diving into tackles instead of tracking runners. I can only apologies to our fans.
What can I say? We're devastated.
You have to credit the opposition for such an amazing comeback, I suppose. But we should be embarrassed by our performance. Once they scored, we went to pieces.
Was the pressure too much?

You must have been confident of reaching the semi-finals after winning the first leg. But you've been completely outplayed today and allowed the opposition to stage an incredible comeback. What went wrong?
They had nothing to lose.

At this stage of the competition, it's about being mentally strong. The opposition had nothing to lose but I think our lads went out there thinking they could just sit in and see out the tie. But once we went behind in the game, we panicked and lost our shape completely.
We were over-confident.

With that big lead from the first leg, I think the boys thought the tie was over. We weren't ready, psychologically, for a battle and the opposition took charge. Too many of our players just went missing. We couldn't get the one goal that would probably have seen us through.
We must remember how this humiliation feels.

Of course the opposition are celebrating an incredible comeback. But we know it's us who've thrown away a place in the semis. We have to be strong now and make sure nothing like this ever happens to us again.
You were overrun today. What happened?
It seemed your boys were so close to reaching the Final. But the opposition have pulled off an incredible comeback. Can you put your disappointment into words?
We couldn't handle the occasion.

I think some of the boys were over-confident after winning the first leg. They just thought we could sit back, see the game out, and we'd be through. But this is a team game. If we're not in it together, terrible things can happen. It's heart-breaking.
We can't make excuses.

Credit to the opposition. They showed great spirit and it was a great comeback. But we were awful, so sloppy, especially when they were coming at us. Once they scored, we were under pressure and couldn't cope. We've only ourselves to blame for what's happened.
It's never over till it's over.

We did so well getting this far in the competition and we'd given ourselves a great chance of reaching the Final. But we were completely outplayed today. I'm angry with the boys but I'm very disappointed for them, too.
Beaten badly in the second leg, how upset are you to be out?
To throw the tie away like that must be even worse because you had a lead from the first game. Were the boys over-confident? How can you explain what happened today?
I'm partly to blame.
I'm partly to blame.

I thought we'd make it through and picked a team that was too defensive, I think. I should have trusted the boys to be positive and put the tie beyond reach but, instead, the opposition took charge of the game. It was an incredible comeback by them.

I thought we'd make it through and picked a team that was too defensive, I think. I should have trusted the boys to be positive and put the tie beyond reach but, instead, the opposition took charge of the game. It was an incredible comeback by them.
We put ourselves under pressure.

It was a terrible performance. Credit to the opposition but we've thrown the tie away, really. After winning the first leg, we thought we could just sit back and see this game out. We put ourselves under pressure, gave away the initiative, and you see what's happened.
We'll never forget this defeat.
I hope our boys remember how this feels. We just didn't compete today and that allowed the opposition to pull off an incredible comeback. We have to make sure nothing like this ever happens again.
